174:/* 
175:    Memory Bank Selection Logic:
176:
177:    During a write operation the CPU will indicate via the SIZE0-1 and A0-1 pins the number of bytes being written
178:    and the location of the writes on theh 32 bit databus.  It is possible for the CPU to write to a single byte location 
179:    inside of a 32 bit wide memory.  As such we need to have individual control over which part of the data bus is 
180:    participating in a write. 
181:
182:    It is important to note that for cacheable areas of memory (which in our design is all of the SRAM and 
183:    DRAM areas) - All read operations are 32 Bus Access, and all read operations must return all 4 bytes based 
184:    on the address bus.  This is to guarentee the cache always has the correct full 32 value for an addresss.
185:
186:    SEE DATASHEET for TABLE
187:
188:    For 32bit Bus Write Access:
189:            BA32_LL = Active high flag for the LSB 8 bits, located on D31:D24
190:            BA32_LH = Active high flag for the second LSB 8 bits, located on D23:D16
191:            BA32_UL = Active high flag for the lower MSB 8 bits, located on D15:D8
192:            BA32_UH = Active high flag for the upper MSB 8 bits, located on D7:D0
193:
194:    For 16bit Bus  Write Access:
195:            BA16_LL = Active high flag for the LSB 8 bits, located on D31:D24
196:            BA16_LH = Active high flag for the MSB 8 bits, located on D23:D16
197:
198:    For 8bit Bus  Write Access:
199:            BA8 = Active high for all accesses, so hard coded to 1, located on D31:24
200:
201:*/
202:
203:BA32_LL = (!CPU_AA0 & !CPU_AA1);
204:BA32_LH = !((CPU_AA1 # (!CPU_AA0 & CPU_SIZ0 & !CPU_SIZ1)));
205:BA32_UL = !(( (!CPU_AA1 & CPU_SIZ0 & !CPU_SIZ1) 
206:            # (CPU_AA1 & CPU_AA0) 
207:            # (!CPU_AA0 & !CPU_AA1 & !CPU_SIZ0 & CPU_SIZ1)
208:           ));
209:BA32_UH = (   (CPU_AA1 & CPU_SIZ1) 
210:            # (!CPU_SIZ1 & !CPU_SIZ0) 
211:            # (CPU_AA0 & CPU_SIZ1 & CPU_SIZ0) 
212:            # (CPU_AA0 & CPU_AA1)
213:          );
214:
