265:    or 8 bits.
266:
267:    This logic relies on the xxxx_REGION_ACCESS variables above to know which combination of DSACK signals to apply.
268:    Since in this initial system both the DRAM and SRAM are 0 WS, the logic will always assert the correct DSACK
269:    combination as soon as the above xxxx_REGION_ACCESS variables are active.  That should happen directly after the 

