488:
489:/*  
490:    Once the refresh requested signal is high, we will wait for an opportunity to start the refresh cycle.  We need to wait 
491:    for the bus to be free.  We will accomplsish this by waiting the AS to be high during a rising CPU clocked combined
492:    with the REFRESH_REQUESTED also being high.  This will set the REFRESH_ACTIVE flip flip on in the condition that we are 
493:    at least 1/2 cycle away from another AS low, which is enough time for the DRAM_REGION_ACTIVE flag to be disabled (to
494:    prevent DRAM access during a refresh).
495:
496:    REFRESH_ACTIVE.d also has REFRESH_ACTIVE as in input, when means once the flip flop goes to 1, it will stay 
497:    there until the reset activity happens.
498:    
499:    This flag is used in the DRAM_REGION_ACTIVE to prevent DRAM access as soon as this flag is active.  That will force the insertion of waitstates
500:    by the CPU until the REFRESH is complete and a DRAM transaction can start.
501:
502:*/
