508:/*  When REFRESH_ACTIVE goes high, it is time to do a refresh cycle.  We will use a 3 bit counter to count CPU cycles.
509:    This state machine will be held in reset until the REFRESH_ACTIVE flag goes active.  At that point it will start counting 
510:    CPU cycles.  Since this state machine is clocked on the falling clock edge, and the ACTIVE signal is clocked on the rising clock edge
511:    this machine will go to state 1 exactly 1/2 a CPU cycle after the ACTIVE flag is set.
512:*/
